{
  "stem": "4113.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "That's how I learned chanting, you know, one and one is two, and two and two is four.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And he would, you know, do the bookkeeping.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my grandmother, my grandfather, when they were still alive, on Thursday they started baking for the Sabbath.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And since we are all, more or less, were in one of two rooms, you know, I mean the smell of that stuff was absolutely fantastic.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then my uncle had a huge tree, a pear tree-- huge one.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we used to pick up those pears and dry them in the oven.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a very, as you would call, heimish and-- and Jewish.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was a very pleasant life.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And of course, we had a river in our town.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The Wislok River was the name of it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we used to go swimming.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You didn't take lessons of swimming.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You learned swimming on your own when you almost drowned, then you knew how to swim.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Anyway, that's how the days went on, day after day.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, a few of them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My cousin-- I have a first cousin who now lives in Manchester.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He survived when he joined the Polish army in exile.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's called the Anders' Army, and he fought in the Middle East.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was at North Africa and then in Italy.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he how-- then married a girl from Poland who was studying in England.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And when he was demobilized in England, he just married there and stayed there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Now, he was with me in school.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there were about two or three others.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There were 40 some kids in the class.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had friends that were not Jewish, but Jewish kids, especially like myself from an Orthodox family, did not really fraternize with gentile kids.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
